Generated C output from the self-host toolchain (lexer.hexa + parser.hexa + type_checker.hexa + codegen_c2.hexa merged). SSOT is the .hexa sources under self/; this file exists only as the boot image for building hexa_v2 without a circular dep on hexa_v2 itself. Cannot be ported to .hexa (it IS the output of porting).

R1 (HEXA-FIRST) compliance: NOT a violation. This .c file is an artifact, not hand-written source. The four .hexa modules are the authoritative source of truth. Regeneration pipeline: `hexa cc --regen` (self/main.hexa:cmd_regen_cc, bt 50 Phase C). Archive plan: bt 50 Phase E will relocate this file under self/native/archive/ once the regen pipeline reaches fixpoint (blocked by bt 34/35). See shared/hexa-lang/build-toolchain.json#50.

Identical disposition applies to siblings lexer_v2.c / parser_v2.c / type_checker_v2.c / codegen_c2_v2.c (each carries its own .hexanoport marker). Hand-maintained C in this repo is limited to self/runtime.c (hexa runtime primitives: GC, value tags, string ops) which is NOT a porting target.
